Use Public Sector Case Analytics Prebuilt Dashboard

After you create Public Sector Case Analytics, navigate to the app and use its dashboards to measure your team’s effectiveness and improve services delivery.

Open the app. From the app picker, select CRM Analytics Studio to open the CRM Analytics home page.
Under Browse in the left column, select All Items. Select the Apps tab, then click your app to open it.
Click Dashboards to see a list of all app dashboards. Public Sector Case Analytics prebuilt dashboards contain best practices that help you get value from your Salesforce data—fast.

The dashboards let you manage service cases and forecast and understand key business performance drivers, visualize trends, and assign actions. They also help you get fast answers to questions about your service business’s results.

Public Sector Case Overview: Summarizes key performance indicators (KPIs) about your case load.
Case Changes: View cases with the most changes and see their average duration in each status.
Case Owner Activity: Helps determine how well case owners use their time.
Case Owner Performance: Shows case manager team performance against key activity and client satisfaction metrics.

Other available dashboards are:

Case Origin Review
Case Variances
Client Review
Customer Satisfaction (if CSAT data is added to your app)
Knowledge Impact (if knowledge data is added to your app)
Knowledge Use (if knowledge data is added to your app)
Omni-Channel (if Omni-Channel data is added to your app)
Prioritize Open Cases
Telephony (if telephony data is added to your app)
title: Using Public Sector Case Analytics Dashboards
